1. Download the ZED SDK based on your system:

	https://www.stereolabs.com/developers/release#82af3640d775


2.	https://www.stereolabs.com/docs/installation/linux 
	
	$ cd path/to/download/folder 
	$ sudo apt install zstd
	$ chmod +x ZED_SDK_Ubuntu22_cuda11.8_v4.0.0.zstd.run
	$ ./ZED_SDK_Ubuntu22_cuda11.8_v4.0.0.zstd.run



3. Check the CUDA and CUDA tookit:

	https://www.stereolabs.com/docs/installation/linux
	
	
4. Check :  

	ZED SDK (see Installation section)
    	Python 3.6+ (x64)
    	Cython 0.26+
    	Numpy 1.13+
    	OpenCV Python (optional)
    	PyOpenGL (optional)
    	
    	
    	$ python -m pip install cython numpy opencv-python pyopengl
    	
    	$ cd "/usr/local/zed/"
	$ python3 get_python_api.py
